parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in extended stopping distances, accidents, or even complete brake failure.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaks
puddles of brake fluid under the vehicle
sudden loss of brake pressure
inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning ABS systems can cause unintended activation, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Unwanted ABS activation
brake pedal vibration
sudden loss of brake pressure
inability to stop the vehicle
jerking or lunging of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake booster failure can cause a loss of brake power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or even complete brake failure.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
sudden loss of brake pressure
inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Severe corrosion and rusting of the front frame extensions, particularly in the area of the steering box mounting, can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and integrity.

particularly in the area of the steering box mounting
making the vehicle unsafe to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken tailgate support cables can cause the tailgate to fall suddenly, potentially causing injury or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not properly protected.
